nl.tno.stormcv.model

Class Frame

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tno.stormcv.model.CVParticle
      • nl.tno.stormcv.model.Frame
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<CVParticle>

    public class Frame
extends CVParticle
    A CVParticle object representing a frame from a video stream (or part of a frame called a Tile). Additional to the fields inherited from CVParticle the Frame object has the following fields:
    • timeStamp: relative timestamp in ms of this frame with respect to the start of the stream (which is 0 ms)
    • image: the actual frame represented as BufferedImage (may be NULL)
    • boundingBox: indicates which part of the original frame this object represents. This might be the full frame but can also be some other region of interest. This box can be used for tiling and combining purposes as well.
    • features: list with Feature objects (containing one or more Descriptor) describing aspects of the frame such as SIFT, color histogram or Optical FLow (list may be empty)
    A Frame can simply function as a container for multiple Features and hence may not actually have an image. In this case getImageType will return Frame.NO_IMAGE and getImage will return null.
    Author:
    Corne Versloot
